</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urubiconoffelwithe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rubicon of Felwithe</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=" http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/31/01 7:34:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Horses in Luclin?!?!</span><hr size=1> Um, paladins have not received any &quot;legitimate upgrades&quot; as you put it because it doesn't fit Verant's plans and because they can't see the forest for the trees, not because some of us have suggested having a horse.  *sigh*<br>
<br>
From the thread on Westwood Tavern at Stratics:<br>
<br>
&quot;I'll answer these questions with the information I have from the article. Horses can't be hurt or killed, can't attack/defend, but you can cast and attack on the horses(you have to still stay still to cast spells). They're the equivilant of jboots(not sure on the speed, but not faster than sow) that look neat, some mobs will have horses. <br>
<br>
There will be different horses you can buy, and the neater looking and faster, the more expensive. Small races get horses that are pony like, medium sized, regular horses, large, war horses.&quot;<br>
<br>
AND<br>
<br>
&quot;I got home today to find the latest Computer Games mag waiting, and what is on the cover? FV riding a horse! <br>
<br>
In the article, etitled &quot;The Horse Whistler&quot;, they detail how small races will get ponies, humans and mid-sized get horses, and large races get warhorses &quot;the size of Clydesdales&quot;. Also noted is that the mounts cannot be targeted or killed, so basically they are not mobs or creatures, just a visual extension of you &quot;wielding&quot; a horse (like an item). They add to your speed, so essentially they are really expensive Jboots as Zargon said. <br>
<br>
The intent is to have different grades of horses selling for different prices, with more desirable ones having better speed or possibly other modifiers. Horses will only be available in Luclin, but once purchased it sounds like they will be useable in ALL outdoor zones. No city or dungeon zones though. <br>
<br>
The article makes it sound like horses are &quot;summoned&quot;, as you can put them away and take them out at any time. When not in use, they simply dissapear (um, what type of container do I need to store my horse in??). They are NOT going to be useable for storage or anything other than extra speed and visual impressiveness. <br>
<br>
One extra cool note, MOBS will get horses too, so expect to see some mounted orcs and bandits (or who knows what) scattered about after Luclin goes live. &quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm no VAK, I just like the idea.  Complain about it if you want - if it doesn't show up, that's okay too.<br>
<br>
